4GL expressions contain values, are values, or produce values as a result of 
processing.  For detailed information and examples of valid expressions, refer 
to the Forms-based Application Development Tools User Guide.  The various types
of expressions are:

  * Constants (strings, numerics, and NULLs)
  * Simple fields on a form
  * Table-field columns on a form
  * Hidden fields and columns
  * Database retrievals through query statements
  * Values returned by procedures
  * Arithmetic and string expressions
  * Logical (boolean) expressions
